This paper is likely to belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category as it deals with video streaming and quality optimization. It also involves network communication and adaptation, which could place it in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. The paper also mentions the use of dynamic programming, which is a common technique in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a client-side buffer, which could be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. However, given the focus on video streaming and quality optimization, the Multimedia category is the most likely.
